                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Conference/272: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-19T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 19, 1937—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>306. Your 554, November 19, 9 p.m. was received after the dispatch of our 305,
                    November 19, 2 p.m.</p>
                <p>We assume from your paragraph No. 3 that the procedure outlined in our 305 would,
                    at the present time, have no chance of success and should not be attempted. If
                    we are wrong in this assumption, please advise. In the meantime, we are advising
                    the British Ambassador here of the substance of your 554 and of this reply
                    thereto.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
